    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, can you help me understand the difference between a \"confidentiality period\" and a \"survival clause\" in a standard contract? I'm trying to make sure I don't miss anything important.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A confidentiality period and a survival clause are two distinct provisions in a contract. A confidentiality period typically restricts the use of confidential information by a specified individual or entity for a set period after the contract ends. A survival clause, on the other hand, ensures that certain terms or obligations continue to apply even after the contract has terminated. This is often used to cover post-contractual warranties or guarantees.",
      "source": "target",
